-- MRF's Three Plants Stop Tire Production After Workers Strike, Union Says
-- B y   G a n e s h   N a g a r a j a n
-- 2010-10-12T04:55:08Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-12/mrf-s-three-plants-stop-tire-production-after-workers-strike-union-says.html
Indian tire maker MRF Ltd.’s plants
in Arakkonam, Puducherry and Thiruvuttiyur were halted because
of a strike by the workers, C.R. Prabhakaran, general secretary
of the employees’ union, said in Chennai today.  MRF’s Vice President of Marketing Koshy Varghese couldn’t
be reached on his phone for a comment.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ganesh Nagarajan in New Delhi at 
